        </div>

        <h2 id="examples">Real hyperlocal SEO examples</h2>

        <h3>1. Multi-location restaurant chain — 60% GBP impression increase</h3>
        <p>A restaurant group applied hyperlocal SEO across 12 locations, creating neighborhood-specific content for each and building citations on neighborhood business association sites and local community pages. Over one quarter, Google Business Profile impressions increased 60% across the portfolio. The locations in neighborhoods with dedicated hyperlocal content outperformed locations without it by 3x on impression growth.</p>

        <h3>2. New hair salon vs established competitor</h3>
        <p>A new salon opened in a neighborhood with an established competitor. The new salon invested in hyperlocal SEO — neighborhood-specific GBP categories, content referencing local landmarks, and citations on neighborhood websites. The established competitor had stronger domain authority but no neighborhood-specific optimization. Within 5 months, the new salon appeared alongside the competitor in Local Pack results for neighborhood proximity searches.</p>

        <h3>3. Emergency service provider — 3-5 weekly calls from zero</h3>
        <div class="url-flow">
